    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Sound of Silence</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ann J Kirschner letter suggests restaurants refrain from playing any music at all (Jan 3 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Is music in restaurants a sore issue? It certainly is. (''Music and Food? The Pros Step In,'' Jan. 3.) Here's a novel idea: no music at all. What makes dining in Paris such a joy is not only the food but the blessed absence of music that diners don't get to choose and the volume of which they can't control.</p>
        <p>Ann J. Kirschner  Brooklyn, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
